# Fluff Date: 2026-03-15 20:33:02
<overview>
<p>The Water Elemental mining suit was a sophisticated submersible exoskeleton developed by Clan Goliath Scorpion for deep-sea industrial operations. Produced at the Hades Industrial Complex on Dagda beginning around 2842, the medium-weight design gave its operators the strength, mobility, and environmental protection needed for underwater mineral extraction and construction work at extreme depths. Though conceived as a purely civilian tool, the Water Elemental proved to be the most consequential industrial development in Clan history, providing the technical and engineering foundation from which all Clan battle armor would eventually descend.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>Powered by myomer musculature and sealed against extreme underwater pressure, the Water Elemental mining suit achieved its remarkable performance through a network of synchronized micro thrusters linked to thousands of pressure sensors woven into the inner lining. Simple gestures from the operator translated into precise thrust commands, allowing the suit to reach speeds rivaling dedicated submersible transports. The thruster array could also lock the suit motionless against strong currents, enabling precision work in turbulent conditions. Additional buoyancy control devices and depth sensors prevented dangerous rapid ascents while monitoring remaining power and air supply.</p><p>As a purely industrial design, the suit carried no weapons. Its equipment loadout included cutting torches, an industrial drill, a basic manipulator for material handling, and a searchlight for low-visibility operations. Two hundred kilograms of standard armor protected the operator from environmental hazards, though this protection was never intended to withstand directed weapons fire. On land, the suit managed only modest walking speed, with its design optimized entirely for underwater mobility.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>Smaller four-trooper work crews proved effective in confined mining tunnels and narrow underwater passages where the standard five-trooper formation was impractical. Clan Wolf also employed reduced-size teams during their early examination of the suits, before developing the formal doctrine that would eventually produce the Elemental battle armor.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>Clan Goliath Scorpion's extensive underwater holdings demanded specialized equipment for deep-sea mineral extraction and construction. Around 2842, Scorpion scientists at the Hades Industrial Complex on Dagda produced the Water Elemental mining suit, a submersible exoskeleton that gave its operators far greater capability than any conventional diving apparatus. The suit's powered frame allowed workers to perform complex underwater tasks at depths and durations previously impossible. The Scorpions treated these suits as unremarkable industrial tools, deploying them across their underwater mining colonies with little thought to military applications.</p><p>That changed around 2860, when visiting Clan Wolf forces on Dagda learned of the Scorpions' mining programs and the exoskeletons powering them. A Wolf Star Captain, recognizing the suits' combat potential, issued a Trial of Possession for one of the units. Point Commander Sarah, assigned the defense, chose her ground carefully. She selected nearby wetlands featuring deep waterways, aggressive fauna, and treacherous footing. Clan Wolf bid a Star of jump infantry against Scorpion operators in their mining suits. Sarah exploited the terrain to devastating effect, using the Water Elementals' aquatic mobility to isolate and eliminate the Wolf warriors piecemeal. The Scorpions lost only a single pilot in the engagement.</p><p>Despite the Trial's outcome, Clan Wolf remained determined to acquire the technology. Through merchant caste trade channels, the Wolves obtained Water Elemental suits and began studying their military potential. Engineers added armor plating, jump jets, and weapon mounts to the basic exoskeleton frame. By 2868, these modifications produced a functional combat suit that Clan Wolf first deployed against the Nova Cats. The Elemental battle armor had been born, a design that would reshape Clan warfare for centuries. Clan Hell's Horses subsequently won the technology through Trials of their own, bringing their genetically bred Elemental phenotype warriors into the partnership of suit and soldier that defined Clan powered infantry.</p><p>The mining suit's influence extended far beyond the Elemental itself. While Clan Wolf pursued a general-purpose combat design, the specialist prototypes developed during early weaponization experiments inspired an entire family of role-specific suits. The Gnome, Salamander, Sylph, and Undine each traced their conceptual lineage back to those early variants, with the Undine being the most direct descendant of the original underwater design.</p><p>Throughout these developments, the Goliath Scorpions continued producing Water Elemental suits at the Hades Industrial Complex for their original mining purpose. Star Commander Vikram demonstrated the unmodified suits' latent combat potential during the Golden Century, pressing a Star of Water Elementals into service on Circe against Clan Mongoose in an unusual underwater engagement. Armed only with industrial tools against scuba infantry, Vikram's forces won a hard-fought battle in flooded terrain, with fierce currents and the exoskeletons' bulk proving as deadly as any weapon. Production at the Hades Industrial Complex continued under Goliath Scorpion control through the Jihad era. Following the Wars of Reaving, Clan Star Adder absorbed Scorpion holdings in the Homeworlds, and the Dagda facilities passed to new management, though the mining suits continued to serve their original industrial purpose.</p>
</history>

